### ===========================
### BOLA (Broken Object Level Authorization) Tests
###
### Test flow:
###   Step 1. Login as Trainer A → create resources → capture IDs
###   Step 2. Login as Trainer B → attempt to access Trainer A's resources
###   Expected: 404 for all cross-trainer access attempts
### ===========================

### -----------------------------------------------
### 0. Register Trainer A
### -----------------------------------------------
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
    "name": "Trainer A",
    "email": "trainer-a@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!",
    "confirmPassword": "Password123!"
}

### -----------------------------------------------
### 0. Register Trainer B
### -----------------------------------------------
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
 
{
    "name": "Trainer B",
    "email": "trainer-b@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!",
    "confirmPassword": "Password123!"
}
 

### ===============================================
### STEP 1 — Trainer A: Login & Create Resources
### ===============================================

### [1-1] Trainer A Login
# @name loginA
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "trainer-a@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!"
}

###

@tokenA = {{loginA.response.body.accessToken}}

### [1-2] Trainer A: Create Member
# @name createMemberA
POST http://localhost:3000/api/members/register
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Member of A",
    "phone": "01011112222",
    "sessionPassName": "10-Session Pass",
    "sessionPassTotalSessions": 10,
    "sessionPassPrice": 600000,
    "sessionPassValidDays": 60,
    "paymentType": "CARD",
    "paymentStatus": "PAID"
}

###

@memberIdA = {{createMemberA.response.body.id}}

### [1-3] Trainer A: Create Session Pass
# @name createSessionPassA
POST http://localhost:3000/api/session-pass
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "20-Session Pass",
    "totalSessions": 20,
    "price": 1100000,
    "validDays": 120
}

###

@sessionPassIdA = {{createSessionPassA.response.body.id}}

### [1-4] Trainer A: Create Membership
# @name createMembershipA
POST http://localhost:3000/api/membership
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "memberId": "{{memberIdA}}",
    "sessionPassName": "30-Session Pass",
    "sessionPassTotalSessions": 30,
    "sessionPassPrice": 1600000,
    "sessionPassValidDays": 180,
    "paymentType": "CARD",
    "paymentStatus": "PAID"
}

###

@membershipIdA = {{createMembershipA.response.body.id}}

### [1-5] Trainer A: Create Schedule
# @name createScheduleA
POST http://localhost:3000/api/schedule
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "memberId": "{{memberIdA}}",
    "membershipId": "{{membershipIdA}}",
    "scheduledAt": "2026-05-01T10:00:00.000Z",
    "sessionDuration": 60,
    "status": "SCHEDULED"
}

###

@scheduleIdA = {{createScheduleA.response.body.id}}

### [1-6] Trainer A: Create Expense
# @name createExpenseA
POST http://localhost:3000/api/trainer-expense
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenA}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "category": "RENT",
    "amount": 1000000,
    "memo": "Trainer A studio rent",
    "paidAt": "2026-05-01T00:00:00.000Z"
}

###

@expenseIdA = {{createExpenseA.response.body.id}}


### ===============================================
### STEP 2 — Trainer B: Login
### ===============================================

### [2-1] Trainer B Login
# @name loginB
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "trainer-b@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!"
}

###

@tokenB = {{loginB.response.body.accessToken}}


### ===============================================
### STEP 3 — Trainer B: Access Trainer A's Resources
### Expected: 404 for all
### ===============================================

### [3-1] Member — GET → 404
GET http://localhost:3000/api/members/{{memberIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-2] Member — DELETE → 404
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/members/{{memberIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-3] Session Pass — GET → 404
GET http://localhost:3000/api/session-pass/{{sessionPassIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-4] Session Pass — PATCH → 404
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/session-pass/{{sessionPassIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "price": 1
}

### [3-5] Session Pass — DELETE → 404
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/session-pass/{{sessionPassIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-6] Membership — GET → 404
GET http://localhost:3000/api/membership/{{membershipIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-7] Membership — PATCH → 404
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/membership/{{membershipIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "paymentStatus": "REFUNDED"
}

### [3-8] Membership — DELETE → 404
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/membership/{{membershipIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-9] Schedule — GET → 404
GET http://localhost:3000/api/schedule/{{scheduleIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-10] Schedule — PATCH → 404
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/schedule/{{scheduleIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "ATTENDED"
}

### [3-11] Schedule — DELETE → 404
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/schedule/{{scheduleIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-12] Trainer Expense — GET → 404
GET http://localhost:3000/api/trainer-expense/{{expenseIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [3-13] Trainer Expense — PATCH → 404
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/trainer-expense/{{expenseIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "amount": 1
}

### [3-14] Trainer Expense — DELETE → 404
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/trainer-expense/{{expenseIdA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}


### ===============================================
### STEP 4 — List Endpoints: Trainer B should see only own data
### Expected: empty array [] or only Trainer B's own resources
### ===============================================

### [4-1] Members list → should NOT contain Trainer A's members
GET http://localhost:3000/api/members
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [4-2] Session Pass list → should NOT contain Trainer A's session passes
GET http://localhost:3000/api/session-pass
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [4-3] Schedule list → should NOT contain Trainer A's schedules
GET http://localhost:3000/api/schedule
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### [4-4] Trainer Expense list → should NOT contain Trainer A's expenses
GET http://localhost:3000/api/trainer-expense
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}
